# Description of the Model

## Model Architecture

Our approach is a hybrid model that integrates 3 molecular representations:

1. **Uni-Mol2** (Transformer, [https://openreview.net/forum?id=64V40K2fDv\&noteId=J41KhtPFiO](https://openreview.net/forum?id=64V40K2fDv&noteId=J41KhtPFiO))  
2. **PAMNet** (GNN, [https://www.nature.com/articles/s41598-023-46382-8](https://www.nature.com/articles/s41598-023-46382-8))  
3. **Molecular fingerprints** (MACCS, ErG, and PubChem)

![][image1]  
We initialize the Uni-Mol2 encoder with publicly available pre-trained checkpoints (84M or 164M). During fine-tuning, all model parameters (Uni-Mol2, PAMNet, and the fingerprint branch) are updated end-to-end. 

## Training Data

We fine-tune our models **only on the official training dataset** released by the organizers: [https://huggingface.co/datasets/openadmet/openadmet-expansionrx-challenge-train-data](https://huggingface.co/datasets/openadmet/openadmet-expansionrx-challenge-train-data)

**We do not use external/private datasets** or perform any additional pre-training. The only pre-trained component is the publicly released Uni-Mol2 checkpoint.

## Training Strategy

**Preprocessing.** We follow the data preprocessing pipeline provided in the organizerâ€™s tutorial, without additional steps.  
**Splitting.** We use a 5-fold scaffold split.  
**Target-specific modeling.** We train separate models (and, when appropriate, different input target groups) for different endpoints to better match task-specific characteristics:

| Target | Training data |
| :---- | :---- |
| LogD | LogD |
| KSOL | LogD, KSOL, MLM, HLM, Efflux, Papp |
| MLM | LogD, KSOL, MLM, HLM, Efflux, Papp, MPPB, MBPB, MGMB |
| HLM | LogD, KSOL, MLM, HLM, Efflux, Papp, MPPB |
| Efflux | LogD, KSOL, Efflux, Papp |
| Papp | LogD, KSOL, Efflux, Papp |
| MPPB | LogD, KSOL, MLM, HLM, Efflux, Papp, MPPB |
| MBPB | LogD, KSOL, MLM, HLM, Efflux, Papp, MPPB, MBPB, MGMB |
| MGMB | LogD, KSOL, MLM, HLM, Efflux, Papp, MPPB, MBPB, MGMB |

**Model selection.** We select the final configuration based on performance on the public leaderboard, using it to choose the best-performing model variants.

# Performance comments

Adding the fingerprint branch yields a notable improvement for Efflux and Papp. For other endpoints, fingerprints provide limited gains; however, the Uni-Mol2 \+ PAMNet backbone already achieves performance comparable to our final submissions.

**Unsuccessful Attempts:**

We explored several alternatives that did not lead to improvements, including:

* Descriptor-based machine learning baselines and some features from commercial software packages.  
* Adding GAFF2 atom types as an additional descriptor.  
* Imbalance-aware training via Label Distribution Smoothing (LDS) to mitigate long-tailed label distributions: LDS weights were computed per endpoint after preprocessing (inverse to a smoothed label-density estimate) and applied during loss computation.
